Dear Collector,

Mr. and Mrs. Theron L. Hedgpeth of northern California, founders of Durametal Products, began their collection in the 1930s and 1940s, and amassed objects of outstanding provenance and quality. Their collection, offered online by Associate Witherells.com, comprises well-documented late 19th and early 20th century European and American furniture and decorative arts, such as Meissen and Sevres porcelain, Tiffany and Lalique glass, and painted porcelain plaques and miniatures.   Click the link below to go directly to the sale.

https://news.sothebys.com/cgi-bin2/flo?y=eEuX0DBy5t0OX0BC8Q0AM

Among the highlights in this special auction is the Louis XV style cylinder desk with an important provenance, dating to the 1880s . Also of interest is a large Meissen porcelain allegorical ewer depicting Water and dating from the late 19th century, after a design by J. J. Kaendler.   Highlights from The Hedgpeth Collection will be on exhibit at Sotheby's New York galleries, November 3 - 8.  Visit the sale now; bidding ends on November 13.

https://news.sothebys.com/cgi-bin2/flo?y=eEuX0DBy5t0OX0BC8Q0AM


We hope you enjoy building your collection with us online.


Sincerely,

